Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges
(no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer.
Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to
coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Pop the @British chicken breasts{2} onto another baking tray. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle} and season with half the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Rub the flavours all over the chicken to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Bake the chicken on the middle shelf of the oven until cooked, about
~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== BBQ Sauce ==

In the meantime, pop the @tomato ketchup{1}, @soy sauce{25%ml},
@Worcestershire sauce{7.5%ml}, @sweet chilli sauce{32%ml},
remaining @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @sugar{1%tsp} into a large #saucepan{}.
Heat gently until the sugar has melted, stirring occasionally, then increase
the heat to medium and bubble until thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Season with a good grind of @black pepper{grind} then remove from the heat and
set to one side.

== Chilli Salsa ==

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}, discard the core and seeds. Chop into
1cm pieces. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Trim, then
thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Zest the @lime{1}, cut into wedges. Halve
the @green chilli{1/2} lengthways, de-seed and finely chop. Slice lengthways
into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut
it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out
the insides onto a #board{}. Chop into 1cm pieces. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Pop the chopped peppers, chilli, lime zest, spring onion, avocado and half the
coriander into a #bowl{}. Add a squeeze of lime juice, a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir together well and set aside.

== Assembly ==

Once cooked, shred the chicken breast into long pieces using 2 #forks{} then
stir into the homemade BBQ sauce in the pan. Coat well.

When the wedges are ready, transfer to an ovenproof #dish{}. Switch your oven
onto grill and set it to high.

Spoon the pulled BBQ chicken on top of the fries. Sprinkle the cheddar cheese
all over the top then pop under the grill. Grill until the cheese is golden
and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the cheese has melted, remove the loaded fries from the grill and sprinkle
over the chilli pepper salsa and the remaining coriander. Add a dollop of
@soured cream{75%g} on top and serve with any spare lime wedges on the side.
Dig in!